Description:
    Creates a new basic Azure App Service Mobile App.

    You can create an Azure Mobile App and run it locally on
    all platforms.  Use the SQLite3 Driver (which is included
    by default) for local development.

Options:
    Jasmine or Mocha for testing

Example:
    yo azure-mobile-apps

    This will create:
        Standard Project Files
            .gitignore
            jsconfig.json
            package.json

        Application Files
            server.js
            server/app.js
            server/logger.js

        Example Controllers
            tables/example.{js,json}
            api/example.js

        Tests
            test/app.js
            test/logger.js

    You can use NPM commands to run the server:
        npm start   Starts the server
        npm test    Runs the tests
